[30;1m259 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m260 | [0m[35mA binary programming formulation was proposed by Pritsker et al. [PWW69]_.[0m
[30;1m261 | [0m[35mIn this formulation, decision variables :math:`x_{jt} = 1` if job[0m
[30;1m262 | [0m[35m:math:`j` is assigned to begin at time :math:`t`; otherwise, :math:`x_{jt} = 0`.[0m
[30;1m263 | [0m[35mAll jobs must finish in a single instant of time without violating precedence constraints[0m
[30;1m264 | [0m[35mwhile respecting the amount of available resources.[0m
[30;1m265 | [0m[35mThe model proposed by Pristker can be stated as follows:[0m

[30;1m221 | [0m[35moptimization problem that consists of finding a feasible scheduling for a set of[0m
[30;1m222 | [0m[35m:math:`n` jobs subject to resource and precedence constraints. Each job has a[0m
[30;1m223 | [0m[35mprocessing time, a set of successors jobs and a required amount of different[0m
[30;1m224 | [0m[35mresources. Resources may be scarce but are renewable at each time period.[0m
[30;1m225 | [0m[35mPrecedence constraints between jobs mean that no jobs may start before all its[0m
[30;1m226 | [0m[35mpredecessors are completed. The jobs must be scheduled non-preemptively, i.e.,[0m
[30;1m227 | [0m[35monce started, their processing cannot be interrupted.[0m

[30;1m221 | [0m[35moptimization problem that consists of finding a feasible scheduling for a set of[0m
[30;1m222 | [0m[35m:math:`n` jobs subject to resource and precedence constraints. Each job has a[0m
[30;1m223 | [0m[35mprocessing time, a set of successors jobs and a required amount of different[0m
[30;1m224 | [0m[35mresources. Resources may be scarce but are renewable at each time period.[0m
[30;1m225 | [0m[35mPrecedence constraints between jobs mean that no jobs may start before all its[0m
[30;1m226 | [0m[35mpredecessors are completed. The jobs must be scheduled non-preemptively, i.e.,[0m
[30;1m227 | [0m[35monce started, their processing cannot be interrupted.[0m

[30;1m156 | [0m[35mOptimizing and Querying Optimization Results[0m
[30;1m157 | [0m[35m--------------------------------------------[0m

[30;1m1 | [0m[35m"""This example reads a MIP (in .lp or .mps), solves its linear programming[0m
[30;1m2 | [0m[35mrelaxation and then tests the impact of adding different types of cutting[0m
